This paper is primarily focused on network queue management for home Internet gateways, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the issue of bufferbloat, which is a security concern related to network congestion control and could potentially fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of flow hashing and filtering of TCP ACKs, which are topics related to algorithms and data structures (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the need for per-user fairness and de-prioritization of background traffic, which could fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses bandwidth shaping and overhead compensation, which could fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
